5:
May darkness and the shadow of death claim it for their own.\q May a cloud live over it;
\q may everything that makes the day black truly terrify it.


\q

6:
As for that night, may thick darkness seize it.\q May it not rejoice among the days of the year;
\q may it not come into the number of the months.
\q

9:
May the stars of that day's dawn be dark.\q May that day look for light, but find none;
\q neither may it see the eyelids of the dawn,
\q
